Since at the current stage we are not able to fully launch the import substitution mechanism, as well as to increase the self-sufficiency of the Russian market due to domestic production, the retaliatory sanctions will continue to carry the risks of the growth of the inflation component.
If you add to this the fiscal reasons related to the lack of confidence in the national currency, as well as the worsening prospects for economic growth, inflation may well exceed 8% by the end of this year.
Alexander Razuvaev, Director of the analytical department "Alpari"
In the 1990s, inflation sometimes reached 20-30% per month, at zero it was also above the current level, another thing that was then compensated for by rapid economic growth.
By the end of the year, inflation will be 8-8.5%.
Plato Magouta, asset manager of the Magouta Foundation
The external factor related to sanctions against Russia is still successfully restrained, but if there is a further increase in pressure, especially on the financial sector, it can lead to certain difficulties and increase inflation expectations of the population, which are usually manifested in purchases of cash in order to secure their savings.
It can be assumed that the government, the Central Bank of the Russian Federation and the Ministry of Finance will try to mitigate the smooth weakening of the ruble, both by market methods and by state regulation.
But price increases traditionally begin after the summer slump and may become more noticeable this fall.
The target level of consumer inflation in Russia at 7.5% is likely to stand, as the Russian Federation still has financial savings.
