The Ministry of Economic Development wants to accelerate the growth of the market of electric cars
This week, the Ministry of Economic Development will bring to the government an integrated plan for the development of environmentally friendly transport in Russia, said Oleg Pluzhnikov, the deputy director of the department of the Ministry at the round table held by Vedomosti at the Moscow Motor Show in 2014.
The plan is commissioned by the government and one of the main goals is to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.
It is expected that the document will be adopted in late September - early October, says Pluzhnikov, the proposed measures concerning electric cars and hybrids - a plan for the development of vehicles on gas-powered fuel in Russia already exists.
The plan (a copy is available at Vedomosti) is designed for 2014-2017.
Criteria for the evaluation of electric and hybrid transport are to be developed and how to stimulate the use and production of environmentally friendly vehicles.
The report to the government, which will describe tax and customs measures to support electric transport, will be prepared by December 2014; the scheme of preferential lending and preferential leasing will appear by April 2015; and proposals to reduce the price of machines, stimulate localization and create a service infrastructure will be developed in 2015.
In 2014-2015, it is planned to make changes to the regulatory acts to facilitate the conditions for the construction of charging infrastructure (in parking lots, gas stations, etc.).
In addition, federal officials intend to formulate proposals for regional authorities during 2015 to also encourage the use of environmentally friendly transport - in the form of giving it an advantage in traffic and parking, for example; and by February 2016 - and proposals to expand public procurement of such transport.
Finally, by October 2014, the Ministry of Economic Development will include in the list of indicators of evaluation of the activities of regional authorities criteria that reflect the effectiveness of supporting the production of environmentally friendly transport, the development of charging infrastructure.
The market of electric cars in Russia is still being formed - in 2013 around 100 electric cars were sold throughout the country.
In early 2014, the import duty on electric cars was zeroed, so sales will amount to about 500 pieces, predicts the CEO of Mitsubishi Motors in Russia Andrey Pankov.
But the five-fold growth does not make electric cars in any way noticeable: in 2013, according to the Association of European Business, 2.78 million cars and light commercial vehicles were sold in Russia.
Currently, only Mitsubishi Motors imports electric vehicles to Russia.
Renault is preparing to start importing – the company is primarily focused on corporate customers, says the director of strategic planning and partnerships Renault in Russia Nicolas Remis.
Most other manufacturers of electric transport took a waiting position with regard to Russia.
The development of electric cars is also at the Russian manufacturers - "GAZA", ", but the output is poor.
For example, in January-July 2014, according to the "ASM-holding", "AvtoVAZ" produced 30 electric cars.
Demand is low due to the expensiveness of electric cars, admits the director of AutoVAZ for engineering Sergey Amanov, without state support there will be no breakthrough in this segment.
The development of the Russian market of electric cars in addition to the expensiveness of cars (the electric cars sold in Russia, on average, twice as expensive as analogues with internal combustion engines) restrains the indevelopment of charging infrastructure (refueling - units), sighs the genera
Due to the cost and the low rate of cost reduction, electric cars in the next 3-4 years will remain a niche segment of the Russian market, predicts the editor-in-chief of Author Mikhail Podorozansky, Celikov agrees with him.
Automakers, on the contrary, say that some models of electric cars are already close to the cost of conventional ones.
The Russian electric car market has good prospects, the main thing is to instill confidence in consumers that "electromobility" is real; this, in particular, will contribute to the emergence of more and more new charging stations, emphasizes the president of the BMW Group in Russia Wolfgang Schlimme.
Such infrastructure projects are implemented, for example, by the state-owned company "Rosseti": several stations have been built in Moscow, about 80 more will soon appear.
Negotiations on the construction of a network of filling stations are also underway with other regions.
According to the director of the department of “Rossets” Vladimir Sofia, the company believes in the market of electric cars and is ready to build filling stations throughout the country, but there are also problems: a small number of electric cars in the country and the lack of a single standard for charging electric cars of different brands.
In addition, "Rosseti" as a network company have no right to engage in the sale of electricity, it is working out the possibility to do this with regard to the charging of electric vehicles.
Pankov believes that the most effective measure of state support for the formation of the market of electric cars in Russia is the abolition of customs duties.
The zero rate will be valid until the end of 2014, the possibility of its extension and extension of the preferential list is being worked out.
Replacing transportation tax with environmental (the idea is discussed and applies to all cars) will also support the market, but not as noticeable as customs preferences, Pankov believes.
Transport tax in Russia is low, says Pankov, unlike, for example, Norway, where the tax cut has led to a sharp increase in sales of electric cars - now they account for 12% of the market.
In Russia, incentive measures are also needed for car owners, such as free parking in the city center (as they have already done in Moscow), Pankov is sure, or the possibility of moving electric cars on designated lanes, which is not yet available in Russia.
