The creator of Coming Out Simulator will release a game about modern journalism
Game designer Nikki Case, famous for the game Coming Out Simulator decided to release a game about modern journalism.
He spoke about his project in an interview with Kill Screen.
Case started working on the game a few weeks ago, but this fact has only now become widely known.
The source of inspiration for the game was the events in Ferguson, where protests are now taking place, which began after a policeman killed an unarmed black teenager.
The focus of the project, which has yet to be named, will be how information coverage of stories affects their consequences.
The hero of the game, a civilian journalist, will need to photograph what is happening in the areas where there are clashes between the police and the population.
The hero can photograph what is happening in different ways, which will affect the course of events.
If he shoots the scene in such a way that the police will look like heroes, and the protesters will look like bandits, the police will start to treat him better and let him go where the ordinary man cannot go.
If he covers events differently, his photographs could turn peaceful protests into a massive uprising.
Points in the game will need to be scored with the help of the hero's Twitter, in which new subscribers will appear, if the photos posted there will prove popular.
The game has no name yet.
The release date and the platform on which it will appear are unknown.
Case, however, has published an image showing how an event can change depending on how a photograph of it is taken and processed.
In an interview with Kill Screen, Case explained that he had been thinking about the concept of such a game for a long time, but initially wanted to dedicate it not to protests in the United States, but to events in the Gaza Strip.
After he started collecting material for the game, the game designer realized that he lacked the knowledge and skills to illuminate the history of the region.
However, when he saw how the media covered the events in Ferguson, he decided to make a game based on the motives of what happened.
Nikki Case is an independent developer who produces browser games.
His most famous project was Coming Out Simulator, which was released in 2014.
This game, which tells the story of events from the biography of Case himself, is dedicated to how a bisexual teenager tries to tell his homophobic parents about his relationship.
